    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Strategy :<br>
The goal of this deck is to reach the site 9 first with your fellowship while opponents fellowship is quite slowed by your mighty isengard minions. This deck also takes advantage of the new cards from Realms Of The Elf Lords, especially Gondor Bowmen and, in a lesser measure, the two citadels : Minas Tirith and Orthanc and Saruman.<br>
<br>
Bid 3 to have great chances to start. You have Sam in the deck, so dont worry about that relatively small amount of burdens. Dont forget to take Aragorn.<br>
<br>
You should play the maximum of tales you can as Aragorn removes 2 twilight tokens each time you move during the Fellowship phase, so The Council Of Elrond will often be for free, and the tales in that deck are quite cheap but effective. Quickly, you should have a decent archery potential. Discard the Gondor Bowmen how often you want, as some cards in the deck allow you to retrieve them. Those cards are Dear Friends ( exert Legolas, Aragorn or Gandalf to do this ) and Fireworks. Fireworks should be used to retrieve the Dear Friends card only and allow you to shuffle your deck so your cards retrieved with Dear Friends shouldnt stay at the bottom of your deck. Citadel Of Minas Tirith will help you to heal a Man ( mostly Aragorn, but it could be Boromir too ). As you may kill many minions during the archery phase, this citadel have its effects very often. PATHS will finish the remaing minions if the game text of the citadel couldnt be used. As you play with many conditions, use Deep In Thought to cancel every conditions except yours. All the cards you play in the fellowship phase are cheap, so opponent wont play lots of minions.<br>
<br>
The Shadow part is classical, but integrates some changes due to RotEL : of course, theres now Saruman, but you also have the Cantea-wannabe Isengard Smith and the Orthanc Berserker, pretty nasty with Worry.  The Tower Of Orthanc adds twilight very often and Abandonning Reason For Madness will allow you to discard useless cards ( such as remaining Councils Of Elrond ) and draw some minions. Because of Saruman, you need less STMTN and SOS.<br>
<br>
With this deck, i think you have a good overview of how decks may be powerful now.  Enjoy ! :-)<br>
<br>
Marc Witch-King THERY.<br>
« Youre brave, little man<br>
But your courage alone will not save you ! »<br>
<br>
